					<div class="eza-caption">A worker spools wire mesh on the factory floor at Riverdale Mills Corp. in Northbridge, Massachusetts. The factory is one of the largest manufacturers of welded wire mesh in the world. Business has been adversely affected by rising costs for materials, due to U.S. tariffs on imported steel.</div>
